{
  "text": "I feel quite prepared. But at the same time, tasks vary a lot so you will always need more time to solve them. Then it is nice to know that you have a lot of knowledgeable colleagues who can support and guide you. (N10) The things that are most important to learn, you cannot learn through reading. So, to participate without having the main responsibility helps and reduces stress. To have an established partner to lean on is important. (P5) For the paramedics, it is more overtly about coping with emotions in order to be able to use medical background and expertise [CITATION_1] . They need to develop experiencedbased and situated knowing in order to concentrate on the job they are supposed to do, instead of panicking, being emotionally stressed and losing sight of the situation. This is focused upon during their socialization, where their relationship with their partner becomes important to their learning processes.",
  "citation_candidates": [
